  "reference": "Numerics @ a2c4dbf. Args convention (this port's own): args = [size, num_pushes, data_flat(num_pushes*size), trailing index/indices]. mean_element appends one row index i (Mean is size x 1); covariance_element/sample_covariance_element/sample_correlation_element append (i, j). sample_covariance_element/sample_correlation_element are curated, not scraped (Test_RunningStatistics.cs only exercises Mean/Covariance, not the SampleCovariance/SampleCorrelation properties): SampleCovariance = Covariance / (N-1) = Covariance/4, an exact-in-binary division (11/4 = 2.75, 10/4 = 2.5); SampleCorrelation's off-diagonal entries reduce algebraically to (10/4)/(2.75) = 10/11 (a repeating binary fraction) since every diagonal entry of SampleCovariance is equal, but the actual code path computes it via Matrix::diagonal + Matrix::sqrt + Matrix::inverse (LUDecomposition) + two matrix multiplies rather than a direct division -- exercising the new LU-backed Matrix::inverse() -- so the curated expected value (0.9090909090909091) was cross-checked against tools/verify_oracles.py rather than assumed equal to the hand-derived ratio.",
